      <p>The <a href="ch70s08.html#MonstersO-R70">pegasus</a> is a magnificent winged <a href="ch73s21.html#MonstersAnimals68">horse</a> that sometimes serves the cause of good. Though highly prized as aerial steeds, pegasi are wild and shy creatures not easily tamed.<a href="img/MonstersO-R.Pegasus.jpg" target="_blank"><span class="inlinemediaobject"><img src="thumb/MonstersO-R.Pegasus.jpg" align="right"/></span></a></p>
      <p>A typical <a href="ch70s08.html#MonstersO-R70">pegasus</a> stands 6 feet high at the shoulder, weighs 1,500 pounds, and has a wingspan of 20 feet. Pegasi cannot speak, but they understand Common.</p>
      <div class="sect4" lang="en">
